make thy way pláin before my fáce. 9 For there is no fáithfulness in their móuth;
their inward párts are very wíckedness. 10 Their throat is an ópen sépulchre;
they flátter with their tóngue. 11 Destroy thou them, O God; † let them perish through their ówn imaginátions;
cast them out in the multitude of their ungodliness; for they have rebélled agáinst thee. 12 And let all them that put their trúst in thee rejóice:
